lines.text: when you were standing in the wake of devastation
when you were waiting on the edge of the unknown
you were there and possibly alone
do you feel cold and lost in desperation?
remember all the sadness and frustration
and in a burst of light that blinded every angel
as if the sky had blown the heavens into stars
you felt the gravity of tempered grace
no one there to catch you in their arms

remember all the sadness and frustration

paragraphs.text: when you were standing in the wake of devastation when you were waiting on the edge of the unknown with the cataclysm raining down insides crying, "save me now" you were there and possibly alone
do you feel cold and lost in desperation? you build up hope but failure's all you've known remember all the sadness and frustration and let it go let it go
